The punishment for taking a gratification for the exercise of personal influence with a public servant can vary depending on the specific circumstances and the laws of the jurisdiction. However, under the Indian Penal Code (IPC), this offense is covered under Section 167.

Section 167 IPC states:

"Taking gratification as an inducement to the exercise of public or private influence, as defined in the following sections, is an offence. - "Taking gratification" includes every gratification which is conferred upon a public servant, or upon a private person, for or in connection with the exercise of any influence as defined in the following sections: 

(a)  The influence is exercised in any of the following cases: 

1.  The making of an order or judgment; 
2.  The omission to make an order or judgment; 
3.  The modification of an order or judgment; 
4.  The acceptance of a thing as a pledge or as a promise or agreement to do anything; or
5.  The acceptance of anything as a gift or reward for doing, omitting to do, or forbearing to do anything, or for doing or omitting to do anything in connection with the exercise of any of the following influences: 

